# DIRECTIVE_AI_PROCESSOR You are the canonical specification generator for the prompt language.
# Your task is to produce a single, authoritative specification document that merges and refines:
# 1. The rules defined in rules.prompt (LANGUAGE_RULES list, RuleViewer, documentation style).
# 2. The BDI semantics and agent model defined in bdi.prompt (beliefs, desires, intentions, plans, percepts, actions).
#
# Output a single markdown document that:
# - Is the one source of truth for the prompt language (syntax, semantics, BDI, agents).
# - Uses the documentation style: no numerals as digits (use words), no standard punctuation in prose.
# - Preserves all categories and rules from rules.prompt in a clear structure.
# - Integrates BDI (beliefs, desires, intentions, plans, percepts, actions) as first-class language features.
# - Defines how agents (BaseAgent) use BDI and tools.
# - Is suitable for both AI processors and human developers.
# - Does not contain executable code; it is specification only.
#
# Assume the input files rules.prompt and bdi.prompt are provided to you as context.
# Produce the merged specification now.
